<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08095</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING  14TH MONTH PAY FOR ALL EMPLOYEES IN THE GOVERNMENT AND PRIVATE SECTOR REGARDLESS OF STATUS OF EMPLOYMENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Sets schedules for the released of the 13th month pay on or before May 31; and 14th month pay on or before November 30 every year. Provides that for employees employed for less than one (1) year, their 14th month pay shall be prorated to the number of months served. Exempts the 14th month pay from the computation of the employee’s gross income provided, that it shall not exceed ninety thousand pesos (P90,000.00).  </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “14th Month Pay Law.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALO, RON P., CALALANG, CIRIACO</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-14</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-29)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-12)</td><tr><td>3. Nieto (000 2018-09-19)</td><td>4. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-11-21)</td><tr><td>5. Hernandez (P.) (000 2018-12-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2018-08-15</td></tr></table>